Code 
library(tidyverse)
library(here)
library(ggridges)
surveys <- read_csv(here( "surveys.csv"))
ggplot(data=surveys, mapping=aes(x = weight, 
                                  y = species)) +  
  geom_jitter(color="tomato", 
              alpha=.5, 
              width=.5, 
              height = .5)+
  suppressMessages(geom_density_ridges()) +
  xlab("weight of rodent in grams")+ 
  ylab("species of rodents")

```{r, messages = FALSE}
library(tidyverse)
library(here)
library(ggridges)
surveys <- read_csv(here( "surveys.csv"))
ggplot(data=surveys, mapping=aes(x = weight, 
                                  y = species)) +  
  geom_jitter(color="tomato", 
              alpha=.5, 
              width=.5, 
              height = .5)+
  suppressMessages(geom_density_ridges()) +
  xlab("weight of rodent in grams")+ 
  ylab("species of rodents")
```
